<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="168" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="9" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,764,789]" pageId="9" pageNumber="168">Discussion.</emphasis>
The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang, Liu" authorityName="Wang, Liu" box="[667,926,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Phlugiolopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[667,796,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="168">P. punctata</emphasis>
Wang, Liu
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[938,960,764,787]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="168">&amp;</emphasis>
Li, 
<number box="[1013,1069,764,788]" pageId="9" pageNumber="168" value="2012.0">2012</number>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bian, Shi &amp; Chang, 2012" authorityName="Bian, Shi &amp; Chang" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Phlugiolopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tribranchis">
<emphasis box="[1130,1286,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="168">P. tribranchis</emphasis>
Bian, Shi 
<emphasis box="[1414,1436,764,787]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="168">&amp;</emphasis>
Chang, 
<number box="[237,296,800,824]" pageId="9" pageNumber="168" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from them in: basal area of male cerci with 
<number box="[915,929,800,824]" pageId="9" pageNumber="168" value="1.0">1</number>
digitiform lobe on interno-dorsal margin and 
<number box="[151,165,836,860]" pageId="9" pageNumber="168" value="1.0">1</number>
semicircular lobe on interno-ventral margin; basal area of subgenital plate comparatively wide, basal margin arch-shaped excavate, lateral margins of subapical area obviously becoming narrower, posterior margin somewhat truncate, the lateral lobe triangular; styli obviously longer than other species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1409,943,968]" pageId="9" pageNumber="168" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,968]" box="[199,1409,943,968]" pageId="9" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,943,968]" pageId="9" pageNumber="168">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species is with reference to the elongate styli of the male subgenital plate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
